checkasm
------------------------------------------
checkasm is a tool for verifying the correctness of assembly code, as well as
performance benchmarking.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libcheckasm-devel-1.1.0-1bl1
  libcheckasm1-1.1.0-1bl1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  meson-1.7.2-1
  nasm-2.16.03-2
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://code.videolan.org/videolan/checkasm

Canonical download:
  https://code.videolan.org/videolan/checkasm/-/archive/v1.1.0/checkasm-v1.1.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack checkasm-1.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./checkasm-1.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/checkasm-1.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/checkasm-1.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcheckasm1-1.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcheckasm-devel-1.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

